Zack Taylor MILLER v. JOHN HANCOCK MUTUAL LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY et al. No. 1278. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Aug. 5, 1935. Sid White, of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. Cohoon & Heiple, of Oklahoma City, Okl., John F. Reinhardt, of Kansas City, Mo., for appellees.

-Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, for failure to prosecute.
